commit.message: Also ignore AttributeErrors which may occur if snappy (not python-snappy) is installed (#34)

Remove unreachable code and undefined name 'seq'

[flake8](http://flake8.pycqa.org) testing of https://github.com/dask/partd on Python 3.7.1

$ __flake8 . --count --select=E9,F63,F72,F82 --show-source --statistics__
```
./partd/utils.py:108:16: F821 undefined name 'seq'
        return seq
               ^
1     F821 undefined name 'seq'
1
```
__E901,E999,F821,F822,F823__ are the "_showstopper_" [flake8](http://flake8.pycqa.org) issues that can halt the runtime with a SyntaxError, NameError, etc. These 5 are different from most other flake8 issues which are merely "style violations" -- useful for readability but they do not effect runtime safety.
* F821: undefined name `name`
* F822: undefined name `name` in `__all__`
* F823: local variable name referenced before assignment
* E901: SyntaxError or IndentationError
* E999: SyntaxError -- failed to compile a file into an Abstract Syntax Tree

commit.message:
BUG: Fixed serialization for Datetime with tz (#25)

* BUG: Fixed serialization for Datetime with tz

We had special-cased (de)serialization for Categoricals, but not pandas' other
extension dtypes. This refactors the special handling to DatetimeWithTZ blocks.

* fixup! BUG: Fixed serialization for Datetime with tz

* fixup! BUG: Fixed serialization for Datetime with tz

* fixup! BUG: Fixed serialization for Datetime with tz

Path management (#24)

* add dir= keyword to File

* Cleanup lingering tempfiles at exit

Add LICENSE.txt to manifest. (#23)

Otherwise, uploads to PyPI are missing the license.

`msgpack.packb` may not have packed utf-8 compatible bytes, so don't … (#22)

* `msgpack.packb` may not have packed utf-8 compatible bytes, so don't assume so in `msgpack.unpackb'.

To reproduce the error, use partd on a numpy array that contains non-utf8 bytes.

* Kinda ugly atm, but use brute force to make tests pass.

I don't know how much this may affect performance when falling back to
pickle is necessary.

* Added a regression test and found a better solution (probably)

* Oups.  That was a pretty bad typo.

Previously, every call to `serialize` was falling back to `pickle.dumps`.
I verified that everything is actually using `msgpack.packb` now.

Fix pandas/numpy serialization (#21)

* Fix pandas/numpy serialization

A bug was introduced in 62a4d48d, which resulted in errors when
serializing multi-indices (as well as other complex index types). This
was caused by two underlying issues:

- False assumption that all indices can be reproduced exactly as
  ``pd.Index(index.values, name=index.name)``
- Partd failing to properly serialize object arrays containing only
  collections (e.g. an array of tuples).

This PR fixes these issues, along with a few other minor fixes:

- Serialize pandas indices separately from blocks
- Properly serialize numpy arrays containing lists/tuples
- Removes unneeded `decode` function for numpy serialization (msgpack
  can do this for us)
- Some pep8 fixes

* Update .travis.yml

- Drop 2.6, add 3.5
- Use conda-forge channel to get recent pandas/numpy for 3.3
- Use conda instead of pip for locket

* Remove python 3.3 as well

It seems python3.3 + pandas > 0.16 is no longer available on
conda/conda-forge.
